String-Based Questions
1. Reverse a string — without using built-ins.
let str:string = prompt("enter the string: ");
let reversed : string = '';
for(let i:number= str.length - 1 ; i>=0; i--){
    reversed += str[i]; 
}
console.log(reversed)

2. Is it a palindrome? Let's find out.

3. Remove duplicates from a string — efficiently.
let str: string = "programming";
let result: string = "";

for (let i: number = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
  let isDuplicate: boolean = false;

  for (let j: number = 0; j < result.length; j++) {
    if (str[i] === result[j]) {
      isDuplicate = true;
      break;
    }
  }

  if (!isDuplicate) {
    result += str[i];
  }
}

console.log(result);  // Output: progamin
